scenarios.situation:
We had an outage yesterday and I need you to turn these raw Slack messages into an incident review summary:

@chen 14:02 — "payments service is throwing 500s, customers can't checkout"
@davis 14:05 — "I see the DB connection pool is exhausted on payments-db-primary"
@chen 14:08 — "scaling up read replicas now"
@martinez 14:11 — "got a customer escalation from Acme Corp, they have a $200k order stuck"
@davis 14:15 — "found it — the nightly analytics job didn't release its connections, been holding 80% of the pool since 03:00"
@chen 14:18 — "killed the analytics job, connections recovering"
@davis 14:22 — "pool back to normal, 500s stopped"
@martinez 14:25 — "Acme Corp order went through, confirming with their account manager"
@chen 14:30 — "we should add a connection timeout to the analytics job and set up an alert on pool utilization > 70%"
@davis 14:31 — "agreed, also maybe move analytics to the read replica so it can't starve production"

Here are the raw Slack messages from our post-incident channel after yesterday's payment processing outage. Please synthesize these into an incident review summary.

@maria 9:02am: payments-api started returning 503s, first alert from PagerDuty at 9:01
@dev-bot 9:03am: deploy pipeline completed for payments-api v2.14.3 at 8:58am
@james 9:05am: I'm seeing connection pool exhaustion in the payments-api logs, max connections hit
@maria 9:07am: rolled back to v2.14.2, 503s still happening
@james 9:12am: found it - the new version changed connection timeout from 30s to 300s, connections aren't releasing
@maria 9:14am: bounced all pods, connections clearing now
@james 9:16am: also noticed we have no alert on connection pool saturation, only on HTTP errors
@maria 9:18am: 503s resolved at 9:15, confirming with checkout team
@sarah 9:22am: checkout team confirms orders flowing again, we lost roughly 12 minutes of orders
@james 9:30am: the timeout change was in PR #4471, it was meant for the reporting-api but got merged into payments-api by mistake
@sarah 9:35am: finance wants to know total revenue impact, I'll pull numbers later today
@maria 9:40am: we should add connection pool alerts and also separate the deploy pipelines for payments and reporting
